def: The small part of a gunstock near the lock, which is grasped bythe hand in taking aim.
The act iif immuring, or the state of being immured;imprsonment.
A miracle worker; -- a title given by the Roman Catholics tosome saints.
To curl or friz, as the hair. [Obs.] Cotgrave.
Exciting appetite; as, appetizing food.The appearance of the wild ducks is very appetizing. Sir W. Scott.
A bush of hair; frizzing of the hair. Clarke.
To annex again or anew; to reunite. "To reannex that duchy."Bacon.
